import json import sys, re import datetime, time import traceback from java.nio.charset import StandardCharsets from org.apache.commons.io import IOUtils from org.apache.nifi.processor.io import InputStreamCallback, OutputStreamCallback from org.python.core.util import StringUtil
class WriteCallback(OutputStreamCallback): def __init__(self): self.content = None self.charset = StandardCharsets.UTF_8
def process(self, outputStream): bytes = bytearray(self.content.encode('utf-8')) outputStream.write(bytes)
class SplitCallback(InputStreamCallback): def __init__(self): self.parentFlowFile = None
def process(self, inputStream): try: # Read input FlowFile content data = IOUtils.toString(inputStream, StandardCharsets.UTF_8) lines = data.split('\n') splits = [] for line in lines: line = line.strip() records = line.split() if len(records) == 26: splitFlowFile = session.create(self.parentFlowFile) writeCallback = WriteCallback() writeCallback.content = line.replace(' ',',') splitFlowFile = session.write(splitFlowFile, writeCallback) splitFlowFile = session.putAllAttributes(splitFlowFile, { 'unit_number': records[0], 'cycle_time': records[1], 'op_setting1': records[2], 'op_setting2': records[3], 'op_setting3': records[4], 'sensor1': records[5], 'sensor2': records[6], 'sensor3': records[7], 'sensor4': records[8], 'sensor5': records[9], 'sensor6': records[10], 'sensor7': records[11], 'sensor8': records[12], 'sensor9': records[13], 'sensor10': records[14], 'sensor11': records[15], 'sensor12': records[16], 'sensor13': records[17], 'sensor14': records[18], 'sensor15': records[19], 'sensor16': records[20], 'sensor17': records[21], 'sensor18': records[22], 'sensor19': records[23], 'sensor20': records[24], 'sensor21': records[25] })
splits.append(splitFlowFile)
for splitFlowFile in splits: session.transfer(splitFlowFile, REL_SUCCESS)
except: traceback.print_exc(file=sys.stdout) raise
parentFlowFile = session.get() if parentFlowFile != None: splitCallback = SplitCallback() splitCallback.parentFlowFile = parentFlowFile session.read(parentFlowFile, splitCallback) session.remove(parentFlowFile)
